## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

This is a textbook case of **"coverage without verification"** — every production method is exercised but almost nothing is asserted on the *outcomes*. These tests will never fail unless the code throws an exception.

---

### Severity-Ranked Findings

#### 🔴 CRITICAL — Assertion-Free Tests (no verification at all)

| # | Test | Problem |
|---|------|---------|
| 1 | `AddProduct_Works` | Calls `AddProduct` then stops. Never verifies the product was stored. |
| 2 | `UpdatePrice_Works` | Calls `UpdatePrice` then stops. Never checks the price actually changed. |
| 3 | `RemoveProduct_Works` | Calls `RemoveProduct` then stops. Never verifies the product is gone. |
| 4 | `GetProductCount_Works` | Captures `count` into a local but never asserts on it. |
| 5 | `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` | Applies 10% discount, never checks any price was reduced. |
| 6 | `ImportFromCsv_Works` | Imports a line, never verifies the product exists afterward. |

**Fix pattern:**
```csharp
// Example: AddProduct_Works → AddProduct_StoresProduct
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_StoresProduct()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);

    var stored = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", stored?.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, stored?.Price);
}
```

---

#### 🟠 HIGH — Trivial `Assert.IsNotNull` (asserts existence, not correctness)

| # | Test | Problem |
|---|------|---------|
| 7 | `GetProduct_Works` | Only checks `!= null` — would pass even if Name/Price were corrupted. |
| 8 | `SearchProducts_Works` | Asserts list `!= null` — would pass with 0 results or wrong results. |
| 9 | `GetAllProducts_Works` | Same — never checks count or content. |
| 10 | `ExportToCsv_Works` | Asserts CSV `!= null` — would pass for `""` or garbage output. |

**Fix pattern:**
```csharp
// Example: SearchProducts_Works → Search_ReturnsMatchingProducts
[TestMethod]
public void Search_ReturnsMatchingProducts()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-002", "Gadget", 19.99m));

    var results = _catalog.Search("Widget");

    Assert.AreEqual(1, results.Count);
    Assert.AreEqual("SKU-001", results[0].Sku);
}
```

---

#### 🟡 MEDIUM — Missing Negative/Edge-Case Tests

| # | Missing scenario | Risk |
|---|-----------------|------|
| 11 | `UpdatePrice` with non-existent SKU | `KeyNotFoundException` path untested |
